'''Camille Howsen''' (1924 - 2012) was an American magician and the mother of football player [[Derek Howsen (V2)|Derek Howsen]]. 

==Early life==
Camille was born in Virginia to a family of popular entertainers, with both of her parents being multimedia actors, performing in film and on stage.

==Magic career==
By the time she graduated high school in 1942, Camille had completed her apprenticeship. After a few more final training lessons over the summer, she became a full-time magician. 

... 

Camille retired in 1990.

==Personal life==
In her teens, Camille met her boyfriend, [[Dennis Howsen (V2)|Dennis Howsen]], a rookie writer and World War II veteran. After the war, they married and had three sons, including [[Donald Howsen (V2)|Donald]] (born 1952), Derek (April 1, 1953 - May 15, 2024), and [[Antonio Howsen|Antonio]] (born 1960). Dennis died in 1994, and Camille followed in 2012. 

